# Validation Rules

## Input Validation Patterns
Always validate requests before processing using sealed class patterns:

```kotlin
sealed class ValidationEvent {
    object Success : ValidationEvent()
    object ErrorFieldEmpty : ValidationEvent()
    object ErrorInvalidFormat : ValidationEvent()
    object ErrorInvalidEmail : ValidationEvent()
    object ErrorInvalidPhone : ValidationEvent()
    object ErrorInvalidSpecialization : ValidationEvent()
    object ErrorPasswordTooShort : ValidationEvent()
}
```

## Validation Implementation
```kotlin
when (service.validateRequest(request)) {
    is Service.ValidationEvent.ErrorFieldEmpty -> {
        call.respond(
            HttpStatusCode.BadRequest,
            BasicApiResponse<Unit>(
                success = false,
                message = "Field cannot be empty"
            )
        )
        return@post
    }
    is Service.ValidationEvent.Success -> {
        // Process request
    }
}
```

## Validation Rules
- **Email**: Valid email format required
- **Phone**: Valid phone number format required
- **Password**: Minimum length requirements
- **Specialization**: Must be valid enum value (UPPERCASE)
- **Marital Status**: Must be valid enum value
- **File uploads**: Validate file types and sizes

## Key Files
- [ValidationUtil.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/util/ValidationUtil.kt) - Contains validation utilities
- Service classes in [src/main/kotlin/service/](mdc:src/main/kotlin/service/) - Implement validation logic